questions.explanation:
.NET Standard emerged to solve the fragmentation problem in .NET ecosystems by defining a set of APIs that are guaranteed to be available across different .NET platforms. It allows developers to write libraries that can be used on multiple .NET implementations without platform-specific modifications.

Example of .NET Standard compatibility:
```csharp
// A library targeting .NET Standard 2.0 can be used in:
// - .NET Framework 4.6.1+
// - .NET Core 2.0+
// - Xamarin
// - Unity
```
